Kalahad brings a few valid points, Wizards are not mad at all about our fellow Magicians, and for several reasons: <br>
<br>
- Focused with draught of Ro or E'ci we can easily outdamage you nuke wise. (1045 dmg focused in 2,5 sec, at very low agro).<br>
<br>
-Aghnar's Thunder is not that hard to get, be it you loot a spectral or buy it; i bought it 80K and never looked back, those 5200k crits are very nice, but i know alot of Wizards who got it already, its only a question of a few weeks before you see it sold for less than 10k in the bazaar.<br>
<br>
-Wizards do crit more than Magicians, if both have maxed AA, about 40-50% more.(you may also have an extra feeling, because we cast our nukes more than you do, so it means more chance to crit).<br>
<br>
-We know that pets are not that usefull in PoP raids, they are just eaten alive with ae spells.<br>
<br>
<br>
For all those reasons, in think its balanced that we have to fight for our most powerfull nukes, as it was always the case anyway.<br>
I think also its balanced that Magicians get FoT on a vendor (although im sure most of you wouldnt have turned down some fun quest to get it); its also fine that you outdamage us in xp groups.<br>
<br>
